criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Prepuberal male and female outpatients, ≥ 5 and < 12 years old in Tanner stadium I
             according to Investigator's assessment;

          -  Clinical diagnosis of mild asthma during at least two months prior to screening visit;

          -  Forced Expiratory Volume during the first second (FEV1) > 80% of predicted normal
             values at screening visit;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Endocrinological diseases including growth impairment or other chronic diseases;

          -  Any concomitant disease requiring additional treatment with topic or systemic
             glucocorticosteroids;
